Identifying the Outcome</span></h2><p><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;">You=
=E2=80=99ve run your A/B test, and now you get to see what happened. There =
are a few possible scenarios:</span></p><h3><span style=3D"font-weight: 400=
;">Scenario 1: One Winning Variation:</span></h3><p><b>What it means: </b><=
span style=3D"font-weight: 400;">One of your variations has outperformed th=
e original (control) version. This is typically determined by reaching a pr=
